            <thetext>The waypoints feature is not able to fire waypoints of a negative scroll position.

We should enhance the waypoints logic to support these values, for making it possible that developers use the waypoints in a &quot;pull-to-refresh&quot; behavior.

Pull-to-Refresh means that user has to scroll to content area too far, above the upper limit, and then an action occurs. This action is very often a HTTP request which refreshes the content of the scroll area.

e.g. :

http://cubiq.org/dropbox/iscroll4/examples/pull-to-refresh/</thetext>
